                            <h3>Three weeks of at-home exercises</h3>
                            <p>During this phase, you will get acquainted the fundamentals of the Ruby programming language. Instructors review your work and provide feedback, or answer questions via video conferencing and e-mail.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="phase">
                        <div class="phase-block block-image phase2-img">
                            <span>2</span >
                        </div>
                        <div class="phase-block">
                            <h2>Phase Two</h2>
                            <h3>Twelve weeks of in-class instruction</h3>
                            <p>We flip back and forth between instruction and exercises. The instructor clarifies a new concept and demonstrates it visually, and then gives an exercise that requires you to use that concept in a different and more challenging context. Students also have time in class to work on their individual Capstone projects, which are shown at our Showcase attended by potential employers.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="phase">
                        <div class="phase-block block-image phase3-img">
                            <span>3</span >
                        </div>
                        <div class="phase-block">
                            <h2>Phase Three</h2>
                            <h3>Six weeks of a paid internship</h3>
                            <p>Our unique internship is a hybrid of continued education and doing work on real projects. Most of the time, you will develop web applications for actual clients (both paid and non-profit) while being supervised and trained by experienced developers. Additionally, you will receive additional curriculum and exercises focusing on more advanced topics helping you develop your skills even further.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
